##Wuhan Doctor Dictation: 1 / 4 Colleague is infected, mask disqualification also arrive ward on time

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. ![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Liu Yiqin, CAIJING reporter

Editor | Sheryl Rong

As of 12:00 on January 31, there were 9,723 confirmed cases, 15,238 suspected cases, 213 deaths, and 178 cured cases of COVID-19. Wuhan is the source of the outbreak of the region, is currently the largest number of patients in the city.

Behind the grim scenes, the biggest concern is hospitals. On January 22, in response to the problem of cross-infection and spread of diseases caused by fever patients seeking treatment in disorder, the Wuhan Government decided on a "7 + 7" model, that is, in the vicinity of seven large hospitals in the urban area, select 7 level-ii public hospitals as designated hospitals for fever clinics, specializing in the treatment of fever patients.

The seven major hospitals are: Tongji Hospital, Xiehe Hospital, Wuda People's Hospital, Wuda Zhongnan Hospital, City One Hospital, city center hospital, city three hospitals. The seven second-level public hospitals are: City Hankou Hospital, City Red Cross hospital, city seven hospitals, city four hospitals West soft area, city nine hospitals, city Wuchang Hospital, city five hospitals.

Most of these hospitals are scattered in different regions in order to bring patients closer to home. Many of these hospitals are not professional infectious disease hospitals. On January 22, the Wuhan Municipal Government issued an emergency task order to transform these hospitals, set up an emergency quarantine.

January 30, the above-mentioned "7 + 7" in a third-tier public hospital front-line doctors accepted the "Caijing" reporter interview. Since the spread of the disease, from January 21, he has not left the hospital for 10 consecutive days, the ward is now full, medical staff overload, there have been cross-infection of medical staff. Recently, with the support teams of hospitals around the world joining, they began to gradually ease the pressure.

Here's what the doctor has to say, or to help the outside world learn more about Wuhan's struggles on the front lines. At the doctor's request, the name of the hospital and the name of the doctor were withheld, and his account was faithfully recorded:

"Ten days, approximately 30 paramedics, seven infected. "

There are 10 doctors and about 20 nurses in our department (the number of nurses is mobile and not fixed) . As of January 29, there were 7 suspected infected nurses in our department alone. If we extend it to the entire hospital, as of January 27, two days before the 29th, 61 health care workers suspected of infection had fever and lung CT problems.

Under normal circumstances, we'd be quarantining the entire hospital, but these are desperate times, and we're running out of staff. At present, the medical staff with mild illness on their own home isolation, two colleagues have been hospitalized, other asymptomatic colleagues are still in normal work.

One of the main reasons for concentrated cross-infection is that we did not do a good job of protection before the pandemic.

On January 16, we admitted an elderly patient to our hospital because of an aggravated condition. He had not yet developed symptoms of pneumonia. We treated him accordingly, and the blood of the patient spilled on the nurse, the nurses were wearing simple protective clothing. On January 18, we began to know about the outbreak, and the patient developed a cough, fever, and immediately had a CT scan of his lungs, which revealed a problem.

In hindsight, we suspected that the patient had infected one of the nurses at the time, and our staff usually worked and ate together, causing a cross infection. The patient passed away two days ago.

Another problem is that we don't have enough protective equipment, and many times we go into contaminated areas without meeting protective standards. All the medical staff in our hospital wear different brands and models of masks.

Last night, I was working the night shift, and before I went into the room, I saw the mask I was issued and I didn't think it was up to code, but I didn't have time to think about it. Our duty cycle is four-hour shift, because masks and protective clothing have to be changed every four hours, if I go in one minute late, the colleagues inside will increase the risk, so I can only put them on immediately, go in. At this point, we are colleagues, but also comrades-in-arms.

After coming out of the ward, I saw a message in the wechat group saying that the mask was just a common dust mask, a material donated from outside, and did not have the medical protection function.

In terms of protective gear, since the outbreak has spread, we have been faced with the problem of not being able to get enough food to eat, and not being able to get enough food to eat, The Hours said.

On 31 January, the latest announcement came that the hospital had decided to keep five doctors in each department on a six-hour shift because of the severe reduction in the number of staff in each department. That's a high risk for a paramedic who has been on the job for 10 consecutive days. But health care workers are not allowed to take time off, and they can not rest until they are infected.

I understand the pressure of the hospital, but I don't want to make fun of my body. Several doctors in the department, including me, although no symptoms, have had chills at night, loss of appetite, biological clock disorders. We have also raised the issue of the timeliness of protective clothing with the hospital leadership and have been told that there is no room for negotiation. There are a lot of posts about the problem that there are many patients in Wuhan who are highly suspected (new coronavirus infection) but can not go to the doctor. From the point of view of the medical staff, we really tried our best until today.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Over the past period of time, we have received a large number of materials from all walks of life fund-raising, very grateful for the support of all walks of life, the shortage of materials has also been eased to a certain extent. But the amount of materials that really meet the hospital's standards is not much. We are on duty after the end of the need to move materials, many materials delivery vehicles can not enter Wuhan, or can not enter the clean area, we are needed to meet.

Now before we receive goods and materials, we will make clear in advance the required models, so as not to waste social resources, but also worried about the enthusiasts to buy fake and shoddy products. Also worried about the issue of material misappropriation. There was a picture in the wechat group that said our hospital's contact number for accepting donations, but the phone number was not ours. We suspected that there was a material fraud problem, we don't know what's going on yet.

"medical support teams have arrived, partially relieving the pressure. "

The first day I went to the fever clinic was January 22, just after the "7 + 7" was finalized. When we received the notification, the government had already released the list of designated hospitals, with little preparation time in between. We had a huge influx of patients that day, but we had to move existing patients, and we had to do some remodeling, so there weren't enough beds available.

Although opened so many hospitals, but the number of patients is too large, the newly opened several hospitals, the first day full. When we get our permits, we leave a number, and we call if there's a bed available, but there are a lot of patients waiting outside the hospital.

On the same day, patients queued for more than six hours everywhere. Many patients were in a bad mood, crying, arguing and cursing, and breaking up in many cases. These days, community hospitals began to divert patients with fever, and major hospitals also opened fever clinics, the situation has eased, but problems remain. When we get our permits, we'll leave a number, and we'll call if there's a bed available.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Although many hospitals are beginning to admit patients, but the number of patients is too large, a large number of patients have been admitted to the hospital bill can not be admitted, only to wait for beds vacant. Compared to the number of new cases per day, the number of cured cases is very small, and many times the beds are available because the patient has died.

When I was in the clinic, a woman told me that her husband was infected, and that he didn't know if he was going to make it through the night, and I looked at the CT scan of her lungs, and I told her that there was an 80% chance that it was new pneumonia, and that it was serious, i wrote her up, but all I could tell her was that there were no beds available and she had to sign in, and she was devastated. Where did the patient go? I don't know.

My classmate's father has a fever for more than a week, symptoms highly suspected, they call me every day to ask can be hospitalized, I have no way, he can only isolation at home, take medicine.

At present, our hospital has opened 600 beds, has been fully occupied, approved to open 800 beds, but also to clean areas, contaminated areas, potential contaminated areas and doctors living areas of the renovation work, so there are only 600.

We now treat patients can only be symptomatic treatment, uncomfortable oxygen, with traditional antiviral drug, there is no specific treatment drugs, patients are very nervous. The health care workers, who are mostly exhausted and working around the clock with little time to rest, still seem to be in a bad way.

I was not until January 29 to know the specific diagnostic process, first department screening, report to the hospital, hospital report to the district. Each department only 3-5 patients a day have the opportunity to test, the first batch of January 29 reported, so far no confirmed results. In other words, the 600 patients in our hospital are still in the highly doubtful stage.

Medical support teams have arrived one after another these days. For the external support teams, the first day is the first day to arrange accommodation, rest, the next day to go directly to the post, to the outpatient clinic or ward for support. At present, out-of-town medical team has been working in the hospital. The arrival of these paramedics, who are specialists in respiratory and critical care, who are more specialized than we are.

But so far, our department has no out-of-town medical support, and the director has been requesting support from the hospital, and nothing has come of it, and our prediction is that the staff in other departments are more nervous and more critical than we are.

Hospital renovation work is continuing, not yet fully up to standard, the follow-up will open some more wards. Our Hospital is not an infectious disease hospital, the relevant medical equipment is not sufficient, but because the designated hospital needs to cover multiple areas, so that patients close to the hospital, our hospital is the largest hospital in the region, so was included in the designated hospital.

At present, the Thor Mountain and Vulcan Mountain hospitals are under construction and will soon be open to the public, and external support is increasing, which gives us new hope. Now we are all living across from the hospital. The hospital has arranged for us to respond immediately. Meals are also provided by the hospital as a unified supply. There are also many donations from restaurants in society. In addition, medical and nursing staff who live far away from their homes, and a fleet of care vans to pick them up.

Experts expect the situation to improve after two weeks, and the general duration of 2-3 months, I believe that is the case, the fight against the epidemic, we are confident.
